      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ASTON ALLURE (4) is racing well without winning, recording three minors on end, the latest hitting the ground running with a fast early sectional but finishing in the minors again when third (35.24) over 600m at The Meadows. Ready to find winning form. BOOTLEG TOMMY (7) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by half a length at Bendigo in a handy 28.80 beating Pocket Riot. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Leading chance again. LARNI LOU (2) has a strong record here including two wins from three starts. In the money last time at Warrnambool (26.08) in a Bottom Up - Grade 5, finishing a neck second. Looks suited here and can measure up. MR. BLUEY LEE (8) can run a bold race on best form.",
